history.content: <md>194-26 doesn't have that much overlap with 182 at all. It goes through more classical computer vision and image manipulation. It serves as a basis for a course like 280 which goes through more advanced and modern computer vision with machine learning. Personally haven't taken 194-26, but this is from what I have heard from other people who have taken the course recently. </md>

I'm currently planning on taking CS 189 next semester and possibly CS 182 later, but I wanted to figure out some differences between these machine learning classes and 194-26 (computer vision & comp. photography). Although I am interested in computer vision, it seems like the class is a subset of 189 and/or 182, where both of these classes already cover many of the foundational topics of computer vision, like convolutional neural networks, classification, object localization, and detection. And after a look at 194-26's website, it seems as if the only other topic covered is "photoshop-esque" image manipulation techniques.

Could someone please tell me what different topics are taught in 194-26 compared to 182/189? I've seen good reviews of the class in terms of fun and interest, but I also don't want to be re-learning too many of the same topics, so this would help me gauge how important it is to take the class in the future.
history.subject: CS 182/189 vs CS 194-26
